    "body": "Close https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/36\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/KMiri-rs/miri/pull/12 fixes the kmiri bug by having the raw pointers in borrow_tracker's expose_tag map, but asterinas will encounter the following UB after the kmiri fix:\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror: Undefined Behavior: in-bounds pointer arithmetic failed: attempting to offset pointer by 128 bytes, but got alloc10351 which is only 64 bytes from the end of the allocation\r\n   --> /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/mm/frame/meta.rs:554:29\r\n    |\r\n554 |         let slot = unsafe { slots.add(i) };\r\n    |                             ^^^^^^^^^^^^ Undefined Behavior occurred here\r\n    |\r\n    = help: this indicates a bug in the program: it performed an invalid operation, and caused Undefined Behavior\r\n    = help: see https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/reference/behavior-considered-undefined.html for further information\r\nhelp: alloc10351 was allocated here:\r\n   --> src/main.rs:18:5\r\n    |\r\n 18 |     ostd::arch::boot::miri_boot();\r\n    |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n    = note: stack backtrace:\r\n            0: ostd::mm::frame::meta::alloc_meta_frames\r\n                at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/mm/frame/meta.rs:554:29: 554:41\r\n            1: ostd::mm::frame::meta::init\r\n                at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/mm/frame/meta.rs:477:39: 477:71\r\n            2: ostd::init\r\n                at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/lib.rs:135:31: 135:54\r\n            3: ostd::boot::start_kernel\r\n                at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/boot/mod.rs:138:14: 138:27\r\n            4: ostd::arch::boot::miri_boot\r\n                at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/arch/miri/boot/mod.rs:73:14: 73:28\r\n            5: miri_start\r\n                at src/main.rs:18:5: 18:34\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo this PR fix asterinas code by replacing `ptr.add` with integer arithmetics.",
